# One-path-per-line manifest of upstream files Fox does NOT ship.
# Applied via `xargs rm -f` after the upstream COPY in packages/integration/Dockerfile.
# Populated incrementally across phases; consumer wired in Phase 7.
#
# Consumer convention: lines starting with `#` and blank lines MUST be
# stripped before piping to xargs. Phase 7 / Phase 8 Dockerfile commands
# use `grep -v '^\s*$\|^\s*#' .fox-removals | xargs -r rm -f --` for this.
# Do not write paths beginning with `#` and do not allow free-form prose
# inline with path entries.
#
# Currently no-ops against the fox fork submodule (these files don't exist
# there — Fox already removed them in past commits). Becomes load-bearing
# at Phase 8 when the submodule re-points at virgin upstream which DOES
# ship these files.

# Phase 2 — upstream onboarding tests Fox replaced with its own wizard:
tests/test_issue1499_keyless_onboarding.py
tests/test_issue1499_onboarding_probe.py
tests/test_onboarding_existing_config.py
tests/test_onboarding_mvp.py
tests/test_onboarding_network.py
tests/test_onboarding_static.py
# Phase 2 — upstream onboarding script (Fox's setup wizard replaces it
# wholesale; api/onboarding.py serves Fox's setup.html instead):
static/onboarding.js
